class Solution {
    public int reverseDegree(String s) {
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);
            int reverseAlphabetIndex = 26 - (c - 'a') + 1;
            sum += reverseAlphabetIndex * (i + 1);
        }
        return sum;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, calculating the reverse degree for each character and summing these values. It uses a constant amount of space, making it efficient for strings up to 1000 characters.
